Rating: 3
I really enjoyed this, though I made it with some modifications based on reviews. It's nice to have another easy recipe for pork shoulder besides BBQ. My changes: - Salted and peppered pork before browning - After browning pork, sauteed green onion pieces with sliced ginger and crushed cloves of garlic. Deglazed with some sherry before putting the hoisin covered pork back in the pan. - Consider adding some orange peel next time. - Defatted sauce and added a little sherry and water to finish.

