I used a bone in pork roast, rubbed it the night before with five spice powder, ginger, garlic, and pepper. The next morning I threw it into the slow cooker with the hoisin, onions, more garlic, red pepper flakes and cooked it on low for eight hours. I used sherry when making the sauce because it was what was on hand and it worked out great. Ridiculous how easy it was in relation to how tasty it was, definite keeper!

