Rating: 4
So good. Will make the following changes next time we make this (and there will be a next time...soon!). Pepper meat before searing instead of using whole peppercorns. Meat may taken more than 3 hours. Judge by fork tearing. Brining in mild salt brine may help produce tenderness in shorter cook time. Strain drippings then pour them into fat seperator. Return onions to defatted drippings, add Cognac and reduce to desired thickness. This one worth doing the work to perfect it to your taste. And, soooooo easy!

