Rating: 2
Decent fusion recipe. it's supposed to evoke the flavors of Peking Duck. Requires some ginger or garlic to reduce 'porky' taste. Added some dry chilies into the sauce to have a bit more depth. Leftovers go well if wrapped in green onion pancakes (cong you bing) with hoisin sauce slathered inside (just the way you'd have peking duck). However, the flavors of this recipe need to be adjusted for someone who wants strong flavor. It's an exciting dish for a midwestern palate. Adequate.

