Rating: 4
Delicious and easy as the ingredients are few- a great fall dish that received rave reviews. Used a 4 1/4 lb boneless pork roast and jar of hoisin (served 4 plus leftovers). Start pork at 400 for first 10-25 min, then lower temp to directed 325. Also, cooked an hour per lb and the roast was falling-apart tender. Scotch drippings/gravy is great, too, and worth the little extra effort.